It&#39;s aping the default export of es2015 modules: when you do `import foo from &#39;foo&#39;;` you are [importing the default export](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/export#Description) of the foo module. 

    // foo.ts
    export default foo;
    
    // otherfile.ts
    import foo from &#39;foo&#39;;

vs a named export

    // foo.ts
    export foo;

